docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, May 22-- The United States joined today with a number of other countries in a quiet but pointed diplomatic boycott of Haitian President Francois Duvalier's celebration of the anniversary of his "re-election" last year.

headline.main: U. S. SHUNS FETE FOR HAITI'S CHIEF; Joins in Boycott to Protest Undemocratic Regime
